UNITED STATES of America, Plaintiff-Appellee v. Terrell M. CLARK, Defendant-Appellant. No. 04-11229. United States Court of Appeals, Fifth Circuit. Decided May 26, 2005. Marc Woodson Barta, Dallas, TX, for Plaintiff-Appellee. Terrell M. Clark, Fort Worth, TX, pro se.

Before GARZA, DeMOSS, and CLEMENT, Circuit Judges.

*530PER CURIAM: *

IT IS ORDERED that the Appellees unopposed motion to vacate the sentence is granted.

IT IS FURTHER ORDERED that the Appellees unopposed motion to remand the case for resentencing is granted.

IT IS FURTHER ORDERED that the Appellees unopposed alternative motion to extend time to file the Appellees brief fourteen (14) days from the Courts denial of the Appellees motion to vacate and remand is denied as moot.

Pursuant to 5th Cir. R. 47.5, the Court has determined that this opinion should not be published and is not precedent except under the limited circumstances set forth in 5th Cir. R. 47.5.4.
